node.text:
Episode 4 MAÍZ is now live! Corn is the heart of Mexican cuisine and culture. It provided the ancient civilizations with the nutrition needed to thrive and prosper. And I think it is one of the most iconically Mexican flavors on any table in this country.  Thank you to @apoloniamex for making this episode come to life! And thank you to the amazing team that makes each episode so incredibly beautiful! ❤️🌽🇲🇽

Show link in my bio!

node.text:
MY BOOK IS HERE! Mi Cocina is ready for pre-order and will be out spring 22’!!!
104 recipes, 32 states, 156 cities, over 20,000 miles. The recipes in Mi Cocina are my spin on the best food I have eaten in my 18-month road trip around Mexico. You can order your copy on Amazon, Barnes and Noble and signed copies are available at Strand and Now Serving. Mil gracias a @chriscristiano @ren_fuller @nidiacueva_stylist @carolinekhwang @morningmourning @davidkoungphoto @el.gamboa for making this book more beautiful than I could ever have imagined! And thank you to @clarksonpotter for making this all happen!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Rick Martinez in New York City, N.Y.. May be an image of skyscraper.

node.text: I moved to NYC in January 2001. I was working in midtown when the towers were hit. The building security moved us onto the lower floors because at that moment all buildings in Manhattan were considered targets. Phones weren’t working, there was no cell service. All my friends were scattered through out the city including one in the path train under WTC and one in an apartment in Battery park. I had no idea where they were and I could not reach them. I snuck back up to my desk on the 14th floor and sent an email to a family friend in New Orleans. I asked her to call my parents who were in court that morning probating my grandfather’s estate and to tell them that I was ok and would call when I got a line through. I sat in a barber shop in the building where I worked, huddled around a phone with all my coworkers, trying to call out to reach our loved ones. When I finally got through, I burst into tears sobbing with my mom and dad. I was lucky and I had it easy. I am so grateful to have been in a city with so many amazing and courageous first responders who gave their lives to save others and to keep the rest of us safe. Thank you to all the firefighters, EMTs and police who got us though that day and the horrible months that followed. I took this pic 10 years ago on September 10, 2011 when the site was being rebuilt. I was also lucky enough to have worked in the new World Trade Center for many years. I will never forget.

node.text: I’m super excited to announce that I am partnering with OXO and will be one of their Chefs in Residence. OXO Chefs in Residence is a brand-new program pairing culinary experts with OXO's innovative tools to bring virtual inspiration to home cooks everywhere. Over the next few months, I'll share the things that excite me in the kitchen and the tools I love and use every day. Stay tuned here and @oxo for my exclusive recipes and tips. **Have a burning kitchen question? Check out @oxo Instagram stories September 7 - 10, and I'll help answer! #ad #oxobetter

node.text: BIRRIA episode 2 of Pruébalo is up! There is not a word to capture how incredibly grateful I am to be working with such talented people. @seabasortega @juanchvz98 @gerry.cruz @diegomedrano @bradacash WE DID IT! You guys are amazing. And HUGE thank you to @the_goat_mafia for letting us tell this story! Link to the video is in my profile!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Rick Martinez on July 10, 2021 tagging @hilarycadigan, @seabasortega, @juanchvz98, @gerry.cruz, and @bingingwithbabish. May be an image of 1 person, ocean, sky and text.

node.text: I AM BEYOND EXCITED! My new show PRUÉBALO is up and I am so proud, so grateful and so happy to be able to show everyone how incredibly beautiful Mexico, Mexicans and the food we eat really is. Huge thank you to @bingingwithbabish for letting me tell this story. 🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾 And to @seabasortega @seabassfilms for your INSANELY GORGEOUS CINEMATOGRAPHY!!! 😍😍😍 And to @gerry.cruz for helping us develop the stories we are going to share. And to @juanchvz98 for your amazing camerawork! I am so full of love atm. Link to the show in my profile!
